The paper analyzes the influence of geographic distance on knowledge flows measured through citations to scientific publications. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), social and information networks (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), software development (cs.SD), and computer systems and technology (cs.CY). However, given that the paper focuses on the analysis of scientific publications, we consider cs.DL and cs.SI as the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.IR, cs.SD, and cs.CY.
